Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main Dialog,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Rendezvous in the blue sky, cuckoo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main Dialog,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Discovery of the Suspect's Body
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:19.91,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't supposed to be \Nlike this, head in my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:26.25,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Struggling to escape from \Nthis saturated world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:32.01,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes like whispering sand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,These circumstances, unchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,gazing out at a dreamless tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:45.81,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna say goodbye to the \Nconfusion of yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:51.23,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,I try reaching out, as if to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:56.95,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,We cry millions of times \Nand then get born again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.16,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with these red eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.37,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,to that pictured future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:08.96,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Come here right by me, \NI'm clapping my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.05,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:15.42,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Strain my eyes in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:21.06,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Can't see anything, don't know \Nanything, but I'll still go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.31,0:01:27.39,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,To the place of shining \Nlight in which you wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.39,0:01:24.98,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 2
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.39,0:01:24.98,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Pitiless{\b0} Song
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.39,0:01:24.98,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi’s\N Meijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Ango Detective Stories)\N"Les Miserables"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.49,0:01:33.82,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Oh, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.82,0:01:36.45,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Everything in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.45,0:01:39.29,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}is reflected beautifully
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.29,0:01:42.08,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's right, this feeling is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.08,0:01:43.67,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.08,0:01:44.08,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,This is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.88,0:01:47.46,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Dol-pli, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.46,0:01:49.05,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Drill pudding?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.05,0:01:50.96,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,It's called an idol app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:52.84,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,A computerized fashion doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.84,0:01:54.93,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,So much is evolving these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.93,0:01:56.89,Main Dialog,GeekA,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't know about it, \Nbut you're standing in line?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.89,0:01:58.31,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,It's my part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.31,0:02:01.93,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I was told to buy the new, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:02.81,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,What is it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.81,0:02:03.77,Main Dialog,Geek2,0000,0000,0000,,Song.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:05.40,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.98,0:02:05.73,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.73,0:02:06.23,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.23,0:02:06.61,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.61,0:02:07.23,Main Dialog,Man1,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.61,0:02:07.23,Main Dialog,Man2,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.23,0:02:07.98,Main Dialog,Woman1,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:08.86,Main Dialog,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,Song!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.86,0:02:11.61,Main Dialog,Geek4,0000,0000,0000,,New tune and new voice data.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:13.95,Main Dialog,Geek4,0000,0000,0000,,It's different than that \Nancient Vocaloid thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.95,0:02:16.82,Main Dialog,Geek4,0000,0000,0000,,It's 100% indistinguishable \Nfrom a real person!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.82,0:02:19.54,Main Dialog,Geek5,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a sample and it \Nwas awesome, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:21.04,Main Dialog,Geek6,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the song was great, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.04,0:02:22.45,Main Dialog,Geek6,0000,0000,0000,,It reminded me of Yonaga'...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.45,0:02:24.25,Main Dialog,Geek7,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't have said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.25,0:02:25.92,Main Dialog,Geek8,0000,0000,0000,,Not supposed to talk about Yonaga'.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.92,0:02:26.88,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:28.25,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Get us in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.25,0:02:32.97,Main Dialog,Geek9,0000,0000,0000,,Only cutesy lyrics and songs that've \Nbeen throughly checked are on the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.01,0:02:34.55,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency Exit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.88,0:02:37.55,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.55,0:02:40.43,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,The Dol-pli expansion data that \Nwas due to go on sale today
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.43,0:02:42.56,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,has been prohibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.89,0:02:46.56,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:47.90,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Don't screw with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:49.52,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,You made us wait in line for hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:51.48,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,You don't do this when you \Nwanna sell something to people!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.48,0:02:53.40,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Prohibited, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:54.74,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,It was canceled, wasn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:56.16,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:57.53,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\c&HFFFFFF&}{\b1}Oyamada{\b0} Arata
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:57.53,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\c&HFFFFFF&}Underground Software Dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:57.78,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,It's a loss for me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:02:59.03,Main Dialog,Prosecutor,0000,0000,0000,,Coming through.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:04.79,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.79,0:03:06.00,Main Dialog,Driver,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:09.67,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,A woman who rode in an unlicensed \Ntaxi told the driver
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:12.92,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,that she forgot an important \Npiece of luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.17,0:03:15.67,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,There's something else \Nthat I have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:19.18,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Driver, would you pick \Nup my luggage for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.68,0:03:20.93,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:26.27,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The driver did as he was told, driving \Nto the place that the woman indicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:30.61,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And that was the mansion of \NYokohama investor Osada Hisako?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:31.69,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,As the woman said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:35.57,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the suitcase was given to him by the \Ngatekeeper at the Osada residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:40.87,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Figuring it was a valuable article,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.87,0:03:42.49,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,he opened it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.33,0:03:48.04,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And inside was the corpse of the \Nmansion's owner, Osada Hisako herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.21,0:03:48.33,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5\fad(300,0)}{\b1}Osada{\b0} Hisako
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.21,0:03:48.33,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5\fad(300,0)}Investor, Victim
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.71,0:03:50.04,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:03:53.88,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Koyama-san, my father is just \Nin the information industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:55.46,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:03:58.68,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right. I'm \Ninterested in this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.68,0:04:00.84,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,This case has so many mysteries
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:02.68,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,that the Chairman is the \Nonly one I could turn to...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:07.60,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the criminal the woman \Nwho took the unlicensed cab?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:07.27,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\a5}{\b1}Kaishou{\b0} Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:07.27,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\a5}Kaishou Rinroku's Daughter,\N Lives at Home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:10.65,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,A different man had left \Nthe suitcase there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.23,0:04:10.27,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\c&HFFFFFF&}{\b1}Koyama{\b0} Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.23,0:04:10.27,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\c&HFFFFFF&}Public Prosecutor, Joint Coordinating Dept.,\N Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.65,0:04:14.61,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There was a memo stating an unlicensed \Ncabbie was coming to pick it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.61,0:04:16.40,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,so to please hold on to \Nthe suitcase 'til then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:19.20,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The gatekeeper tried to refuse, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.37,0:04:25.29,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,We believe Osada Hisako was \Nmurdered outside of her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.29,0:04:29.79,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the murderer, \Nthat man, go to the trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.79,0:04:31.67,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,of stuffing her body into a suitcase \Nand dropping it off at her own mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:35.50,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\a5}{\b1}Kaishou{\b0} Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:35.50,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\a5}Chairman of Japan Justice Network System Holdings
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.67,0:04:35.50,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And what's the connection with the \Nwoman who took the unlicensed cab?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.50,0:04:37.76,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the truth of the matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:43.97,Main Dialog Italic,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The suspect is 47-year-old Aramaki \NToshiji, a restaurant proprietor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.97,0:04:49.77,Main Dialog Italic,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,He became the lover of Osada \NHisako after her husband died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:54.11,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that this \NAramaki has an odd hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:02.41,Main Dialog Italic,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Aramaki's hobby is dressing \Nup in women's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.41,0:05:07.45,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the man that handed \Nover the suitcase and the woman passenger
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:09.79,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,were both Aramaki in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.79,0:05:12.33,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Aramaki's aim was to throw \Nsuspicion off of himself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:16.09,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,by making you think there were \Ntwo criminals working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.09,0:05:19.67,Main Dialog Italic,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,We're currently expending every effort \Nto track down Aramaki's whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.64,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,The city lights are so \Nbeautiful, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.89,0:05:30.81,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Yokohama... Blue Light Yokohama...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:28.64,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\b1}Shinjurou{\b0} Yuuki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:28.64,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)}Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:28.64,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\b1\a5}In{\b0}ga
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:28.64,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\a5}Detective's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:41.07,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever we walk, wherever we walk, \Nit's like being in a small boat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.07,0:05:43.28,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.16,0:05:48.83,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Your voice is so beautiful, \NI couldn't help myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:54.29,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\b1}Osada{\b0} An
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:54.29,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)}Victim's Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.16,0:05:53.96,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. You're the detective, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.75,0:05:59.09,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to find the person \Nwho murdered your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.30,0:06:02.93,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I think I heard Kaishou \NRinroku figured it out days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:06.10,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Aramaki isn't the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:07.93,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,He's in hiding, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:14.19,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,My mother had been threatened \Nby someone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.06,0:06:18.73,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Every month, she delivered \Nmoney to a hotel in Shinagawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:19.82,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Shinagawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:23.07,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Please deliver the suitcase to \Nthe Tokyu Hotel in Shinagawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.53,0:06:26.12,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,That's fishy, Shinjurou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.12,0:06:28.20,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,And who threatened her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:32.50,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe someone from Yonagahime...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.25,0:06:36.04,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:39.09,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure the killer \Nwas someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.25,0:06:47.09,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Understood! Please leave it to this \NDefeated Detective, Yuuki Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:55.52,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,The city lights are so \Nbeautiful, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:56.90,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Yokohama...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:57.94,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,That's the song from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:01.61,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother taught it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:03.15,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.57,0:07:05.15,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,My grandma said that in her country,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:08.74,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,it was illegal to play Japanese \Nmusic on TV or the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.12,0:07:11.16,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But she said that even though \Nthis song is in Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:14.46,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,it became so popular that \Neveryone sang it secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.04,0:07:17.50,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think the power \Nof song is amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:20.38,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to be a singer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:26.18,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. At one point, I thought \Nmaybe it couldn't happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:29.26,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,but you can't give up on \Nyour dreams, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:33.77,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Because one's dreams \Nwill always come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.27,0:07:43.94,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Shinjurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.65,0:07:49.07,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Aramaki is the killer, \Nwhy would he go to the trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:51.33,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,of dropping off the suitcase \Nat the victim's own home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.33,0:07:52.58,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:56.71,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yonagahime... Yonaga'...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:05.59,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,All images and sounds of Yonagahime \Nhave been wiped off the net,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.09,0:08:06.09,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency Exit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.59,0:08:06.88,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,and if you upload something,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:10.26,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be arrested under the New \NInformation Privacy and Protection Act.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:13.43,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,You seriously don't \Nknow about Yonagahime?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:15.35,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I wasn't in Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:19.98,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Dol-pli
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:22.48,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,This is them recreated using Dol-pli.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:24.73,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)}Yonagahime  3+1
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.82,0:08:28.90,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Valhalla Maidenland
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:37.66,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.75,0:08:42.33,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,World, open your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.71,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Dawn is almost here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.71,0:08:49.34,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.59,0:08:52.93,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Shone down upon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.43,0:08:58.23,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,They were supposedly national idols.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:09:02.06,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,Since the war broke out, there wasn't \Na day this song wasn't played on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:04.11,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,The message was "let's strike \Nback against terrorist attacks"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.11,0:09:05.73,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,and "let's dispatch a \Nmassive amount of troops".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:08.57,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,The sentiment was backed by public \Nopinion, so after the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.57,0:09:11.61,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,the Public Prosecutor's office \Nprohibited this song from being broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.99,0:09:13.70,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What's "3 + 1"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:19.96,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,"Yonagahime, 3 + 1". That \Nsums up their entire history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.55,0:09:28.96,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.51,0:09:32.89,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Yonagahime was \Noriginally a four-person group.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.89,0:09:34.35,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,But right before their debut,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:38.56,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,one of the members became a victim of \Nthe first terrorist attack in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.56,0:09:40.73,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,It's referred to as the attack on 12/23.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:44.86,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,And that image was captured \Non surveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:49.44,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,Eri isn't dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.44,0:09:51.36,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,She's with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:54.24,Main Dialog,Sumika,0000,0000,0000,,The four of us are Yonagahime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.87,0:09:58.99,Main Dialog,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to lose or cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:00.75,Main Dialog,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna take back our dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:02.75,Main Dialog,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,Please listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:07.13,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,This made their name \Nrecognition skyrocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.13,0:10:10.63,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,Eri's voice, which had already \Nbeen recorded, was used, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.26,0:10:13.51,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up! (You)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.51,0:10:15.51,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,We must (know)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:17.60,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,depart for there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:20.89,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,On fallen, broken wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.31,0:10:25.06,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,They say that's Eri's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:42.75,Main Dialog,Eitaro,0000,0000,0000,,After Yonagahime broke up, my little \Nsister wanted to have a solo career.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:42.12,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5\fad(300,0)}{\b1}Nakahashi{\b0} Eitarou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:42.12,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5\fad(300,0)}Older Brother of Nakahashi Sumika
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.75,0:10:44.92,Main Dialog,Eitaro,0000,0000,0000,,But Ms. Osada was against it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.92,0:10:47.25,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Osada? You mean Osada Hisako?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.25,0:10:48.13,Main Dialog,Eitaro,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:51.92,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\b1\c&HFFFFFF&}Nakahashi{\b0} Sumika
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:51.92,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\c&HFFFFFF&}Former Member of Yonagahime 3 + 1
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:56.84,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,What connection did Osada \NHisako have with Yonagahime?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:10:59.93,Main Dialog,Eitaro,0000,0000,0000,,She was the president of the \Nagency. The creator of the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:08.23,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The words of love, Yokohama
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.11,0:11:09.57,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.23,0:11:12.69,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Blue Light Yokohama
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:11.69,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are already here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:13.57,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Yonaga'! Yonaga'!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.57,0:11:14.49,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:22.37,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yumeno-san and Kumi-san, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.37,0:11:23.91,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Yonaga'! Yonaga'!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:25.54,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.88,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\b1}Tsunemi{\b0} Kumi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.88,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Former Member of Yonagahime 3 + 1
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.88,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\a5\b1)}Umezawa{\b0} Yumeno
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.88,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\a5}Former Member of Yonagahime 3 + 1
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.54,0:11:29.38,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,The authorities know who \Nkilled Ms. Osada, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.38,0:11:33.46,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, you two met the \Nvictim here once a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:34.38,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.38,0:11:35.51,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I checked into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.72,0:11:37.72,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was being \Nthreatened by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:40.18,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,You have the wrong \Nidea! The president...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.18,0:11:43.89,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Osada was worried about us, \Nso she gave us living expenses...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:48.15,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, if you didn't say anything, you \Ncould be taken for a man, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:52.86,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I hear Osada Hisako's body was \Ncarried by a mystery man and woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.86,0:11:54.15,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:11:56.53,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that we had a \Nhand in the president's death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.53,0:11:57.95,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.95,0:12:00.53,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,No! Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:05.00,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the president's gone, I don't \Nknow what I'll do to make ends meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:10.79,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,At a glance, a man and woman duo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:14.30,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,A Shinagawa hotel and a complicated \Nrelationship with Osada Hisako...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:18.13,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that someone wanted us to \Nthink you two were the culprits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.01,0:12:19.89,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,Someone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:21.76,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll never forget that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.26,0:12:25.47,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What if it's the ghost of Eri-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.56,0:12:27.89,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,Eri died...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:29.23,Main Dialog,Kumi,0000,0000,0000,,in the attack on 12/23.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:33.02,Main Dialog,Tsne,0000,0000,0000,,Yumeno?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.32,0:12:37.07,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Inga!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.70,0:12:43.28,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I can't... I can't hold \Nit in anymore, Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.08,0:12:46.00,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:47.54,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.54,0:12:49.71,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You know very well what I mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.71,0:12:51.63,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the truth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:54.13,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no motive...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:56.76,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get to the bottom of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:04.39,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You said it yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:07.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll show you what a real human is."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.85,0:13:10.98,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll show you human truth."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:15.02,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,All right! But I still \Nhaven't found the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:16.40,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.32,0:13:18.82,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,What are you searching for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:20.95,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to protect?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:23.16,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Sweet Shinjurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:25.91,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,But I feel sorry for that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:28.12,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.12,0:13:31.58,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,If you take pity on yourself, \Nnothing will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:35.04,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me. What should I ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.93,0:13:47.35,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Now... answer me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.35,0:13:50.68,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the real fourth \Nmember of Yonagahime?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:54.31,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not supposed to tell anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.78,0:13:59.03,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing you can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.03,0:14:01.99,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,People have no choice but \Nto answer her question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:03.82,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Just one question...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.11,0:14:05.32,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:08.58,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the fourth member of Yonagahime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.08,0:14:11.12,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:18.80,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,Yonagahime was a three-person group...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:26.14,Main Dialog,WomanInga,0000,0000,0000,,What about Anzai Eri, who was caught \Nup in that terrorist attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:30.85,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,When our debut was decided on, Ms. \NOsada brought that footage with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.31,0:14:35.98,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,She said the story would be \Nthat the girl was one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.98,0:14:38.94,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,She even had vocal tracks laid down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:42.99,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,We never even met a girl named Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:44.95,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,But we couldn't refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.95,0:14:47.32,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,We were told we'd become \Nstars that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.45,0:14:51.50,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,When the war was over, \NYonagahime broke up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:55.04,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,We were told we couldn't \Nsay anything about "Eri".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:56.67,Main Dialog,Yumeno,0000,0000,0000,,If we did...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:14:59.00,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency Exit
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:15:02.05,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The city lights are so \Nbeautiful, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:05.97,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.64,0:15:11.22,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever we walk, wherever we walk...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:23.19,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:25.28,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Why? What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:26.74,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it canceled?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.66,0:15:33.33,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,No good. It's still hard \Nto get a connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.33,0:15:34.37,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,The call got dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:36.58,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,There were two culprits...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:39.50,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,And they often used a hotel in \NShinagawa as a meeting place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:42.09,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,to get money from your \Nmother every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.38,0:15:44.59,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,The people who fit those \Nqualifications like a glove...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:47.01,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,are Yonagahime's \NYumeno-san and Kumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.97,0:15:50.72,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it... Those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:55.68,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But I see... If Kumi-san was in \Ndisguise, she could look like a man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:16:00.73,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you wanted \Neverybody to think, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:04.03,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,But Kaishou picked somebody \Nelse as the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:05.11,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Did you panic?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.57,0:16:07.32,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:10.57,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai Eri is supposed to \Nbe resting in peace here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.91,0:16:13.45,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,But she's really you, Osada An.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:18.46,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,To make Yonagahime's debut \Npossible, Osada Hisako created
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.46,0:16:22.29,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,the fictional identity of a fourth \Nmember who was killed in a terrorist attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:25.09,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,She used recordings of your \Nexceptional voice to back it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.13,0:16:28.38,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I analyzed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.93,0:16:31.89,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Your voice is nearly a perfect \Nmatch with Anzai Eri's,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.89,0:16:34.56,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,and it's also the same voice \Nfrom the Dol-pli expansion data
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.60,0:16:36.93,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,that was prohibited before it \Ncould go on sale the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.48,0:16:38.69,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.14,0:16:41.15,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I was suspicious from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.94,0:16:44.11,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the murderer \Ngo out of their way
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:45.94,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,to hand over that suitcase in \Nfront of the victim's home?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.69,0:16:52.37,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,It was so the person who lived there \Nwouldn't be suspected, right, Osada An?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.46,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to sing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.46,0:16:59.71,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.71,0:17:02.21,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Your singing is wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:08.88,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,I was a child when Yonagahime was \Nformed, so I didn't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:13.05,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't bother me that my voice \Nwas being used for "Anzai Eri".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.43,0:17:16.97,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Since I could hear my \Nvoice on TV every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.77,0:17:20.94,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But after the war was over, \Nthe feeling behind my songs,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.94,0:17:25.40,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,to cheer up a gloomy Japan in the face \Nof defeat in war, all but disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:28.94,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, Mom told \Nme I couldn't sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.94,0:17:31.82,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about me becoming a \Nsinger was all thrown out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.41,0:17:34.66,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't want to give in!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:37.49,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to have faith that \Nmy dream would come true!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:41.00,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I thought the \NDol-pli data would be okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.00,0:17:42.71,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,since my name wouldn't be on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.71,0:17:45.04,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But she said I couldn't \Ndo that either...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.04,0:17:46.63,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,She said if somebody figured \Nout it was the voice of Eri,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.63,0:17:49.47,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,the girl who was supposed to be dead, \Nit would cause trouble for some people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:55.47,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,Mom stole my songs... \Nand Yonagahime from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:57.97,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,For eternity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:18:04.06,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,We are kept in solitude
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.06,0:18:11.49,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna protect the \Nyoung girl who keeps praying
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.49,0:18:15.62,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Making those eyes glisten
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.62,0:18:19.41,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Is the biggest sin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.41,0:18:26.34,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wave her flag of courage with love...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.84,0:18:35.22,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But even that last phone call shot \Ndown my chance at becoming a singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:38.01,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The suspect, Aramaki, was found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:40.27,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It was a crime of passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:42.35,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\b1\c&HFFFFFF&}Aramaki{\b0} Toshiji
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:42.35,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\c&HFFFFFF&}The Victim's Lover
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:42.69,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,When he realized that he couldn't \Nescape, he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.69,0:18:44.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.44,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou's deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.52,0:18:48.40,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer was Aramaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.40,0:18:52.82,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Still, as before, Osada An's \Nvoice will not be made public.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.20,0:18:56.24,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's a measure we're taking under the \NNew Internet Privacy and Protection Act.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:18:57.78,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:02.71,Main Dialog,An,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, then \Nwhat did I kill Mom for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:06.04,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Have you suffered a breakdown?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:07.46,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.21,0:19:11.42,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,People die. Things break down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.42,0:19:12.97,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing is unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.72,0:19:16.22,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,And of course, I will break as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.22,0:19:17.97,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.97,0:19:19.35,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I searching?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.85,0:19:22.39,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm not so important to \Nexist without looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.81,0:19:24.14,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,I search.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:26.10,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.44,0:19:28.31,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,You people created the story
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.31,0:19:31.36,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,that Anzai Eri was a victim \Nof terrorism, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.36,0:19:32.99,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,The footage of Eri was faked, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:37.45,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yonagahime was an idol group formed \Nto raise spirits during the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.45,0:19:40.74,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,But after the war, it would've caused \Nyou trouble if that trick were exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:42.66,Main Dialog,Yuuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:45.21,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. A conspiracy theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.08,0:19:49.92,Main Dialog,Arata,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Get started!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.18,0:19:58.26,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Illegal Data Detected \N File Has Been Deleted
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:21.28,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.28,0:20:22.28,Main Dialog,Geek,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:28.37,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The lights of the city are \Nso pretty... Yokohama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:34.96,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Blue Light Yokohama with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.21,0:20:36.84,Main Dialog Italic,Newscaster,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The murderer of the \Nwealthy Yokohama woman
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:38.43,Main Dialog Italic,Newscaster,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}was correctly deduced \Nby Kaishou Rinroku,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.43,0:20:42.26,Main Dialog Italic,Newscaster,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}the Chairman of JJ \NNetwork System Holdings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.68,0:20:42.14,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.39,0:20:48.39,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Our usual word of love, Yokohama
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.32,0:21:01.70,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Wherever we walk, wherever we walk
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:06.12,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It's like being in a small boat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:10.96,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The way I rock
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.96,0:21:18.72,Song,Song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The way I rock in your arms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.60,0:21:36.15,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,In the pale morning \Nmist, a whispered prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.53,0:21:44.16,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna follow this \Ntwisted landscape with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.58,0:21:52.17,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the "truth", \N"a 'lie' will do" is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.50,0:22:00.55,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing it as if we can see through
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.55,0:22:04.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, beyond words
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:08.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a falling feather
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:11.48,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.39,0:22:16.90,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.21,0:22:36.34,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, unravel it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.34,0:22:40.46,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a tattered cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:43.30,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.18,0:22:48.51,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.31,0:22:53.02,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It says the next episode is \Nbased on "Masked Mansion"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.02,0:22:54.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,from Ango Detective Stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.85,0:22:56.19,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.19,0:23:01.07,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Huh! There's a Mitsuko, Fumihiko, \Nand Kigihiko in the original, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.07,0:23:03.86,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And Komamori, Inamori, \NMizuhiko, Tsuchihiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.86,0:23:06.37,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,How many relatives are there in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.37,0:23:08.87,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Says they've got a disease that makes \Nthem collapse if they see someone's face,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.87,0:23:10.83,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,so they were raised wearing masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.83,0:23:13.00,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What a fresh idea! That's \NAngo Sakaguchi for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.00,0:23:15.12,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, is it okay to do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.12,0:23:16.58,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on UN-GO:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.12,0:23:17.13,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 3
